## Slide 5: Feature Deep-Dive — Smart Onboarding

### 🏠 Household Profile Setup (Not Just "Add a Child")

| Feature | Details |
|---------|---------|
| **Family Members Modal** | Add husband/partner, children, parents (elderly), siblings, in-laws, others — each with dedicated modal |
| **Child Age Stages** | 👶 Toddler (0-3) · 🧒 Pre-School (3-5) · 🎒 School-going (5-17) · 🎓 College (17+) — Eva adapts tasks per stage |
| **School/College Name** | For school-going and college kids — Eva tracks circulars, PTMs, and exam schedules |
| **Domestic Staff Modal** | Add Maid, Cook, Driver, Nanny, Gardener, Watchman — with phone numbers for WhatsApp coordination |
| **Remove Members** | Live add/remove with instant UI update — no static data |
| **Ecosystem Connections** | Gmail (auto-draft emails), Google Calendar (conflict detection), WhatsApp (parse family chaos) |
| **Budget Autopilot** | Set weekly quick-commerce restock budget — under limit = auto-order, over limit = Eva asks first |

> **Why this matters:** Eva adapts its entire behavior based on household composition. A toddler household gets diaper-tracking and pediatrician reminders. A college-kid household gets hostel fee tracking and exam schedules.

