## Slide 8: Feature Deep-Dive — Calendar (Collision Intelligence)

### 📅 The Calendar That Thinks Ahead

| Feature | Details |
|---------|---------|
| **Full Month Grid** | Interactive calendar with color-coded event dots per day |
| **Event Type Colors** | Work (dark purple) · School (warm peach) · Me Time (mint green) · Family (soft pink) |
| **Legend** | Bottom legend mapping colors to event types |
| **Collision Detection** | 🔴 Red badge "1 collision" in header when schedule conflicts detected |
| **Level 1 Collision UI** | Red-highlighted event card: _"Level 1 Collision with 1:1 with Manager (11:00 AM)"_ |
| **Draft Reschedule Email** | Click "Draft Email" → full email template appears: Subject line, body, sign-off — ready to send via Gmail |
| **Call Sitter Modal** | Click "Call Sitter" → WhatsApp call interface with Priya (Backup Sitter) +91 number |
| **Agent Reasoning Notes** | Each event shows Eva's logic: _"Eva postponed from 11 AM to resolve collision with PTM"_, _"Husband GPS shows him near studio at 5:15 PM"_ |
| **Filter Chips** | All · School · Me Time · Family · Work — filter today's events by type |
| **Add Event Modal** | Title, Time input, Type selector with color dots — add to today's schedule |
| **Delete Events** | X button on every event card |
| **Protected Time Blocks** | ☕ "Protected Focus Time" with mint green highlight — _"Eva guarded this block. 2 meeting invites auto-declined."_ |

