## Slide 9: Feature Deep-Dive — Inbox (Chaos Parser)

### 📥 From WhatsApp Chaos → Structured Actions

| Feature | Details |
|---------|---------|
| **Multi-Source Parsing** | WhatsApp messages, Voice Notes, School Documents — all parsed into structured actions |
| **Tab Filtering** | All · WhatsApp · Voice Notes · Documents — categorized inbox |
| **AI-Parsed Actions** | Every raw message gets an Eva-generated actionable suggestion |
| **Accept/Reject Buttons** | Functional accept (adds to planner) and reject (removes from inbox) with live state update |
| **Merge Detection** | Eva detects duplicate requests: _"Eva merged duplicate 'milk' requests. Auto-adding to Zepto cart."_ |
| **Voice Transcription** | Voice notes transcribed and converted: _"Kitchen sink leaking"_ → **Action: "Call Raju Bhai (plumber)"** |
| **Document Extraction** | School circular PDF → extracts 2 events (Republic Day + Fancy Dress) → "Add Both to Calendar" |
| **Flight Itinerary Parsing** | Forwarded flight email → structured: Mumbai→Delhi, March 15, IndiGo, Terminal 2 → auto-add calendar + cab booking |
| **Medication Alerts** | _"Dad's Aztor-20 running low"_ → auto-refill via Apollo within pre-approved ₹800 budget |
| **Agent Reasoning Notes** | Every card shows WHY Eva made that decision — full transparency |
| **Agent Status Indicator** | "Eva — Orchestrating" badge in header with green active dot |
| **Accepted Items** | Accepted items move to a separate "Accepted" section with green checkmark |

