## Slide 11: USPs — Why Eva Stands Apart

### 🏆 Unique Selling Propositions

| # | USP | Existing Apps | Eva |
|---|-----|--------------|-----|
| 1 | **Agentic AI** | Passive reminders, you still do everything | Eva **acts autonomously** — orders groceries, drafts emails, messages staff |
| 2 | **Cognitive Load Scoring** | No app tracks "thinking work" | Decision-weighted scoring: planning > execution. Your mental load is now a number. |
| 3 | **Work-Life Integration** | Separate work tools (Slack) + home tools (WhatsApp) | Single dashboard spanning both worlds — sprint planning next to school PTM |
| 4 | **Household Equity Tracking** | No visibility into who does what | Bar chart proof: "You did 84% of cognitive tasks." Send Splitwise settlement. |
| 5 | **WhatsApp Chaos Parser** | You read every message manually | Eva reads 10+ groups, extracts actions, merges duplicates, creates tasks |
| 6 | **Calendar Collision AI** | You discover conflicts in the meeting | Eva detects conflicts hours ahead, drafts reschedule emails, calls backup sitters |
| 7 | **Staff Orchestration** | You message staff individually in 3 languages | Eva messages maid in Marathi, cook in Hindi, driver in English — from one dashboard |
| 8 | **Corporate Firewall** | You manually cancel 10 meetings for a sick child | One tap: cancel meetings + Slack handover + OOO email + school notify + alert family |
| 9 | **Protected Me-Time** | You never protect personal time | Eva auto-declines meeting invites during guarded focus blocks |
| 10 | **Invisible Finance** | Household spending is untracked | Every rupee tracked, categorized, and fairly split between partners |

