## Slide 13: Why Eva? — The Impact

### 📈 Projected Impact Metrics

| Before Eva | After Eva |
|-----------|----------|
| 40+ decisions/day mentally tracked | **Automated to 8-10 decisions/day** |
| 12-15 hrs/week on coordination | **Saved 12 hrs/week** (Eva handles coordination) |
| ₹15-25K/month untracked spending | **Every rupee tracked and fairly split** |
| 84% cognitive load on one person | **Equity dashboard makes imbalance visible** |
| 3 sick-leave meetings to cancel manually | **One-tap Corporate Firewall handles everything** |
| Zero protected personal time | **4+ hrs/week of guarded me-time** |

### 🎯 Target Audience

| Segment | Size | Need |
|---------|------|------|
| **Working Mothers (25-45)** | 30M+ in urban India | Dual-role burnout, invisible labor |
| **Nuclear Families** | 50M+ households | No extended family support system |
| **Dual-Income Couples** | 20M+ | Equitable task distribution needed |
| **Families with Elderly** | 15M+ | Medication tracking, care coordination |
| **Families with Domestic Staff** | 25M+ | Staff coordination across languages |

### 💡 Why NOW?

1. **AI Maturity** — LLMs can now parse WhatsApp messages, draft emails, and make contextual decisions
2. **India's Quick-Commerce Boom** — Zepto, BigBasket, Blinkit APIs make auto-ordering feasible
3. **Remote/Hybrid Work** — Calendar collisions between work & home are at an all-time high
4. **Mental Health Awareness** — Cognitive load and burnout are now recognized workplace issues
5. **UPI Infrastructure** — Automated payments for staff salaries and vendor bills at zero cost

